fields.description:
Titanium Apps are crashing when object null checks are used inside app.js file.
This is a *regression* since same code works fine in 3.4.1

h5. Steps To Reproduce
1. Create an app using following code
{code}
var b = null;
if (b != null) 
{ 
	// do something
}
{code}

2. Run the App in iOS device with 3.5.0 SDK

h5. Actual Result
App is crashing

h5. Expected Result 
App should not crash.

comments.body:
Following codes are not crashing
{code}
//code 1
var b = 1;
if (b != null) 
{ 
    // do something
}

//code 2
var b = null;
if (b == null) 
{ 
    // do something
}
{code}

Use cases:
KitchenSink -> Base UI -> Window (Standalone) is crashing for same reason with 3.5.0 SDK

Yes [~ingo] It's a duplicate of TIMOB-18118

In TIMOB-18118, It's crashing in the same syntax. 
Following is the actual code of crash in the ticket
{code}
if (null != b && null != e) // It crashes in this line if either 'b' or 'e' is null.
        // some code here
{code}
